# Distributed Workflow Builder — Task Checklist

## Phase 1: Architecture & Design
- [/] Create high-level architecture diagram & service breakdown
- [ ] Define DB schema (PostgreSQL)
- [ ] Define OpenAPI spec for all services
- [ ] DAG engine design document
- [ ] Sandbox runtime design document
- [ ] Trade-off analysis document

## Phase 2: Project Scaffold & DevOps
- [ ] Create monorepo folder structure
- [ ] docker-compose.yml (PostgreSQL, Redis, MinIO, NATS, all services)
- [ ] CI pipeline (GitHub Actions)
- [ ] Linting configs (ESLint, Prettier)

## Phase 3: Backend Services
- [ ] API Gateway (reverse proxy + rate limiting)
- [ ] Auth Service (JWT + refresh tokens, RBAC)
- [ ] Workflow Service (CRUD, DAG versioning)
- [ ] Execution Orchestrator (state machine, DAG runner)
- [ ] Worker Service (horizontally scalable, Redis queue consumer)
- [ ] Plugin Service (registry, versioning, schema validation)
- [ ] WebSocket gateway (real-time updates)
- [ ] NDJSON streaming endpoint (/runs/:id/logs/stream)

## Phase 4: DAG Engine
- [ ] Topological sort + cycle detection
- [ ] Parallel execution with Promise.all
- [ ] IF/ELSE branching
- [ ] Retry with exponential backoff
- [ ] Idempotency key enforcement
- [ ] Pause / Resume / Cancel state machine
- [ ] Deterministic ordering

## Phase 5: Plugin System
- [ ] TEXT_TRANSFORM plugin (Caesar cipher, reverse, SHA-256)
- [ ] API_PROXY plugin (fetch, header injection, cache toggle)
- [ ] DATA_AGGREGATOR plugin (summary hash map)
- [ ] DELAY plugin (blocking/non-blocking)
- [ ] Docker sandbox per plugin execution
- [ ] Resource limits (CPU, memory, timeout)

